## 2026-04-05 - Server connection setup is buried in Settings
- Added prominent inline connection prompt on the Tokens tab (EmptyState) and an expandable inline URL editor in the disconnect banner, eliminating the need to navigate to Settings to configure the server URL:
  1. **`EmptyState.tsx`**: Replaced the minimal "server offline" banner with a full connection setup card when disconnected. The card shows: server icon + status, editable URL input (pre-populated from current serverUrl), "Connect" button with loading state, success/failure feedback, and a how-to-start code snippet (`npx @tokenmanager/server`). New props: `serverUrl?`, `checking?`, `onConnect?: (url: string) => Promise<boolean>`.
  2. **`PanelRouter.tsx`**: Passes `serverUrl`, `checking`, and `onConnect={updateServerUrlAndConnect}` to `EmptyState` (all already available from `useConnectionContext()`).

