## 2026-04-05 - Command palette qualifier autocomplete is static
- Added dynamic value completions after qualifier colons in CommandPalette token mode. When the query ends with e.g. `type:`, `has:`, `generator:`, `path:`, `name:`, `group:`, or `value:`, a completion chip row appears showing actual values from the current token data (e.g. "color", "dimension" for `type:`). Partial values are supported: `type:col` narrows to matching types. Clicking a chip inserts the full qualifier:value into the query and re-focuses the input. Uses `onMouseDown` + `e.preventDefault()` so the input doesn't lose focus before the click fires.
- Added `getQualifierCompletions(qualifier, partial, tokens, groups?)` to `tokenListUtils.ts` вҖ” returns up to 10 completions filtered by partial prefix. Handles `type` (distinct token types), `has` (canonical has values), `generator`/`gen` (distinct generator names), `path` (top-level segments), `name` (leaf names, capped at 30), `group` (all group paths), `value` (top-20 by frequency). `desc` and unknown qualifiers return [].
- Added `ACTIVE_QUALIFIER_RE` regex and `detectActiveQualifier()` helper to detect `qualifier:partial` at end of query string.

