## 2026-04-05 - Search input behavior is fragmented across three systems вҖ” consolidate so command palette is the single advanced search surface
- Unified fuzzy matching: replaced CommandPalette's private simpler `fuzzyScore` (consecutive bonus only, score 0 for non-match) with the shared `fuzzyScore` from `shared/fuzzyMatch.ts` (segment-boundary bonuses, camelCase bonuses, exact-prefix bonuses, -1 for non-match). All `score > 0` call-site guards handle -1 correctly.
- In-tree вҶ’ command palette delegation: added `onOpenCommandPaletteWithQuery?: (query: string) => void` to `TokenListActions`. When `setSearchQuery` is called with a value that passes `hasStructuredQualifiers()` (i.e., contains `type:x`, `has:x`, `value:x`, etc.), the in-tree search clears and the command palette opens in token mode (`">" + " " + query`) instead. Wired through `tokenListTypes.ts` вҶ’ `PanelRouter.tsx` вҶ’ `App.tsx` (inline callback that sets `commandPaletteInitialQuery` + `setShowCommandPalette(true)`).
- SetSwitcher ranked matching: replaced boolean `fuzzyMatch` with `fuzzyScore` from the shared module; filtered results are now sorted by score (highest first) instead of insertion order, making large foldered set lists easier to navigate.

